30/07/2003
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- A spokesman for the UN war crimes tribunal announced on Tuesday (29 July) that the trial of Slobodan Milosevic will resume on 25 August, after the court's summer recess. Hearings were adjourned this week because of Milosevic's illness. This was the ninth interruption since the trial started in February 2002.
In other news Tuesday, UN Secretary General Kofi Annan asked the Security Council to allow him to replace Carla del Ponte as chief prosecutor of the Rwanda war crimes tribunal. She would remain in charge of prosecution in the cases stemming from the 1992-1999 conflicts in the Balkans. (Reuters, AFP - 29/07/03)
